               <p>JOSEPH HAINSWORTH. I know the house of Mr. 
               <persName id="t18310217-90-person980">
                  Thomas 
                  Hannam
               <interp inst="t18310217-90-person980" type="surname" value="Hannam"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-90-person980" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-90-person980" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , in the <placeName id="t18310217-90-crimeloc552">New-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310217-90-crimeloc552" type="placeName" value="New-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310217-90-crimeloc552" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-90-off550 t18310217-90-crimeloc552"></join> - there is a garden in front. On the 12th of February, at six o'clock in the morning, I found the gate open - I walked in with my light; on looking round I saw the two prisoners laying, one on the other, under the garden wall, and two bags of coals near them, containing about three bushels - I called up the family, and Birch came down; I asked the prisoners what brought them there - they made no answer; I know one of them well.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-90-person981">
                  WILLIAM 
                  BIRCH
               <interp inst="t18310217-90-person981" type="surname" value="BIRCH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-90-person981" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-90-person981" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live with Mr. Thomas Hannam. I went to bed about eleven o'clock at night, on the 11th of February; our coal-cellar is in front of the house, but the door was not locked; the coals in the bags were all large ones, and appeared to have been taken off my master's heap - the gate had been broken open.</p>
               <p>JURY. Q. Whose property are the bags? A. I do not know.</p>
